My boyfriend and I took the cocktail class with Daniel in Dec 2020. The class size was small to enforce social distancing. The class was amazing. It was a wonderful evening of making delicious cocktails with fun anecdotes from bartender Daniel. He is so funny and he makes the class memorable. The cocktails we made were: Sazerac, hurricane and Ramos gin fizz. The place is big with stations for everyone. He also did shots with us and taught us different types of alcohol and how to identify good and practices when your bartender makes cocktails for you. After the class we went down to his bar "Victory" and partied there as well. It turned out to be a great fun evening! The best cocktail class I have ever been to!

Being an annual visitor to NOLA, I am still amazed at the things we find.  New Orleans Drink Lab, operated by Daniel Victory, is one that will be on our schedule for years to come.  Having visited at a time when COVID is still affecting business here, it was a treat to be able to still participate - and they took every precaution to make you feel comfortable given the circumstances.  From the beginning you are given a brief, but concise, history of the Lab and cocktails. It is run by 2 of the most talented professionals that one could expect and  the instruction was presented in a fun and humorous manner. The Classic class teaches 4 NOLA drinks. After taking the class, knowing what we were taught, I will never again order these particular drinks without knowing what process the bartender is using.  Taking the class has given me more of an appreciation for what happens behind the bar and more disdain for what doesn't or shouldn't. It has definitely upped my game for home mixing and has me hungry to learn more.  Word of caution-no matter how much of a drinker you are, plan ahead.  If you drive in, have a designated driver - otherwise take some other form of transportation. You WILL be feeling it after the class. Class is 2 hours long and you consume 4  made how they should be drinks (with some judgmental half-shots mixed in). Doing the math-won't pay to drive.  All that said, it, by far, is one of the best experiences we've had so far in NOLA. We thank Camille and Daniel for continuing during such a difficult time!

My friend ordered the 'Bare Necessities' which looked great but I didn't try it. When we got their, it wasn't too busy but as the time passed, it was a full house but we still got great service. I would come back here again just for the Truffle Popcorn!
